---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'February 2026';
---
<Base
  title="Terms of Use | BasisToolkit"
  description="Terms of Use for basistoolkit.com and the SAP Logon Transfer software — licence, disclaimer of warranty, and acceptable use."
  path="/terms/"
>
  <section class="legal">
    <div class="wrap legal-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="muted updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        By using <strong>basistoolkit.com</strong> and the software offered here, you agree to
        these Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the site or the software.
      </p>

      <h2>The software is free</h2>
      <p>
        SAP Logon Transfer is provided free of charge as freeware. You may download, use and
        share it for personal and professional purposes. The software is distributed under the
        MIT License; the licence text is included with the download.
      </p>

      <h2>No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The software and the information on this site are provided "as is", without warranty of
        any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of
        merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and non-infringement. You use the
        software at your own risk.
      </p>
      <p>
        Although the tool writes a backup before making changes and does not handle passwords,
        you are responsible for keeping your own backups of important configuration. In no event
        shall the author be liable for any claim, damages or other liability arising from the
        use of the software.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use this site and software lawfully. You may not attempt to disrupt the
        site, misuse it to distribute malware, or represent the software as your own commercial
        product.
      </p>

      <h2>Trademarks</h2>
      <p>
        BasisToolkit is an independent project. It is not affiliated with, authorised by, or
        endorsed by SAP SE. "SAP" and other SAP product names are trademarks of SAP SE and are
        used here only for descriptive, referential purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Downloads may be hosted on third-party platforms (such as SourceForge), and the site may
        display third-party advertising. Your use of those services is subject to their own
        terms and policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the site after changes
        are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms can be directed through the
        <a href="/about/">About page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .legal-wrap { max-width: 760px; padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
    .legal h1 { font-size: var(--step-3); }
    .legal .updated { margin-top: -0.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .legal h2 { font-size: var(--step-1); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--slate); line-height: 1.7; }
  </style>
</Base>
